For this, it is essential to bring traditional medicinal remedies out of esoteric medical treatises and into scientific manuscripts (
 Harrison et al., 2015; 
 Fuchs et al., 2018; 
 Anonye et al., 2020; 
 Furner-Pardoe et al., 2020). To fully explore this, it is imperative to enable the steady identification and evaluation of traditional formulations with anti-biofilm potential. In the context of traditional medical practices, this starts with probing historical treatises for potential remedies and testing them for anti-biofilm activity (“treatise to test”), following which promising agents can be taken up for further evaluation.
